TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Stochastic Model for Adaptive Behavior in a Dynamic Situation
AU  - Jones, J. Morgan
Y1  - 1971/03/01
PY  - 1971
DA  - 1971/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.17.7.484
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.17.7.484
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 484
EP  - 497
VL  - 17
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A stochastic model of adaptive behavior in a dynamic situation is proposed, and its properties developed. The model is developed from a hypothetical construct of behavior, and, in the limit, becomes a nonstationary probability diffusion process. Although the model has wide potential applicability, it is discussed in the marketing context for which the model was first proposed. In addition to properties of the model, important aspects of the model as it applies to marketing will be discussed.
AB  - A stochastic model of adaptive behavior in a dynamic situation is proposed, and its properties developed. The model is developed from a hypothetical construct of behavior, and, in the limit, becomes a nonstationary probability diffusion process. Although the model has wide potential applicability, it is discussed in the marketing context for which the model was first proposed. In addition to properties of the model, important aspects of the model as it applies to marketing will be discussed.
